lyrics:
Born in a body that doesn’t feel like mine
Holding back the truth for 14 years of my life Society's stigma had me walking blind
But it's time to be me and embrace my pride

I'm breaking down these walls, 
I won't hide anymore
I'll rise above the judgment, 
breaking stereotypes for sure
This is my journey, my story to unfold,
She becomes He and I'll break the mold
style: Songh like Moonlight by Kali Uchis
